SIMPLE: seminal
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seminal
<hw>Sem"i*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>seminalis</ets>, fr. <ets>semen</ets>, <ets>seminis</ets>, seed,
akin to <ets>serere</ets> to sow: cf. F. <ets>seminal</ets>. See
<er>Sow</er> to scatter seed.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to,
containing, or consisting of, seed or semen; <as>as, the
<ex>seminal</ex> fluid</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Contained in seed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>Holding the first place in a
series of developed results or consequents; serving as a source, or
first principle; giving rise to related ideas or results; germinal;
radical; primary; original; <as>as, <ex>seminal</ex> principles of
generation; <ex>seminal</ex> virtue; a <ex>seminal</ex>
discovery.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>The idea of God is, beyond all question or comparison, the one
great <qex>seminal</qex> principle.</q> <rj><qau>Hare.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Seminal leaf</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a seed
leaf, or cotyleden.</cd> -- <col><b>Seminal receptacle</b></col>.
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>Same as <er>Spermatheca</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seminal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Seminal
<hw>Sem"i*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A seed.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seminality</ent>⟦br⟧
